&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ashfield MedComms&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashfield MedComms is a global leader in the medical communications space with a portfolio of clients across medical affairs, publications and commercial. We are part of Inizio Medical, which also includes ApotheCom, Nucleus Global and MEDiSTRAVA. Our position as part of this international network gives us a key advantage over other agencies in terms of the scale of our reach and depth of our expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More broadly, Inizio Medical is part of Inizio, whose mission is to be THE strategic partner for health and life sciences companies. Unparalleled in scale and expertise, we connect a full suite of Advisory, Medical, Marketing/Communications, Patient and Stakeholder Engagement, and Biotech services to reimagine clients&#39; challenges into opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;166&quot; data-end=&quot;570&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;166&quot; data-end=&quot;184&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br data-start=&quot;184&quot; data-end=&quot;187&quot;&gt;As an &lt;strong data-start=&quot;193&quot; data-end=&quot;212&quot;&gt;Account Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you will lead and develop medical affairs and promotional accounts, serving as a trusted client partner and ensuring high-quality delivery across medical communications programs. You will manage day-to-day account activity, oversee budgets and timelines, and collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive client satisfaction, operational excellence, and account growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;166&quot; data-end=&quot;570&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;572&quot; data-end=&quot;596&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;572&quot; data-end=&quot;596&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;597&quot; data-end=&quot;1136&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;597&quot; data-end=&quot;668&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;599&quot; data-end=&quot;668&quot;&gt;Lead client relationships and act as the primary day-to-day contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;669&quot; data-end=&quot;742&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;671&quot; data-end=&quot;742&quot;&gt;Manage medical communications projects from briefing through delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;743&quot; data-end=&quot;825&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;745&quot; data-end=&quot;825&quot;&gt;Collaborate with Scientific, Editorial, Creative, and Project Management teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;826&quot; data-end=&quot;901&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;828&quot; data-end=&quot;901&quot;&gt;Oversee budgets, forecasting, and financial performance across accounts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;902&quot; data-end=&quot;970&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;904&quot; data-end=&quot;970&quot;&gt;Ensure work is delivered on time, on budget, and to agreed scope&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;971&quot; data-end=&quot;1057&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;973&quot; data-end=&quot;1057&quot;&gt;Identify opportunities for organic account growth and support new business efforts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1058&quot; data-end=&quot;1136&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1060&quot; data-end=&quot;1136&quot;&gt;Maintain high standards of quality, compliance, and operational efficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1138&quot; data-end=&quot;1151&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1138&quot; data-end=&quot;1151&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1138&quot; data-end=&quot;1151&quot;&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1152&quot; data-end=&quot;1538&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1152&quot; data-end=&quot;1224&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1154&quot; data-end=&quot;1224&quot;&gt;2–5+ years of healthcare or medical communications agency experience&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;Scientific Director – Publications (Oncology)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashfield MedComms, an Inizio Medical company, is an international medical communications agency. Our reputation for delivering high-quality and creative communication solutions is founded on scientific expertise, strategic understanding and motivation of our staff. As part of Ashfield MedComms, our clients benefit from synergies across our network of offices spanning the US, Europe and Asia Pacific regions. We offer an unrivalled integrated approach to medical communications from across the globe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inizio is expanding its footprint in the publication space and is looking for a senior level director to lead the scientific team and provide strategic account oversight. This is an excellent opportunity to help shape the department and grow the publication team and business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;The right individual must have strong work experience in the publication space (peer-to-peer experience preferred) with a focus on oncology. This is a client-facing role that requires directing client strategy, staff mentoring / management, leading scientific teams in content creation, and partnering with the VPs of scientific and client services and managing director in business development, among other responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage scientific team responsible for delivery of a full range of strategic publication focus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Under the guidance of the scientific VP, lead and manage account to ensure the creation of high quality, accurate medical / scientific content with ability to expand management responsibilities as team grows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and grow publication work partnering with VPs of scientific and client services and managing directors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and develop strategic and tactical business recommendations relevant to client strategy and marketplace needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop / lead / facilitate key strategy workshops&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a high level of comfort articulating scientific and therapeutic information in oncology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster innovation and collaboration across Ashfield MedComms to position agency as leader in publication work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD, PharmD, MD with 10+ years of experience of relevant medical communications experience, with an in-depth understanding of publication oncology work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of successful scientific leadership across several clients/therapeutic categories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;US launch experience required; Global experience is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some travel will be required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing staff / direct reports (potentially based across multiple locations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;This position is open to candidates who are looking for a fully remote or hybrid opportunity based in the United States (east coast preferred).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;In addition to a competitive package, we are known for our friendly and informal working environment. We also offer excellent opportunities for career and personal development, and a robust benefits package including health, dental, vision, 401(K), vacation, holiday, and sick time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Ashfield MedComms&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;proudly offers an equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to driving a culture of diversity, inclusion and belonging where everyone is able to bring each facet of themselves to work each day. At Ashfield MedComms, we believe there is strength in diversity and inclusivity, and that strength is a driver of our success.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ashfield MedComms&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashfield MedComms is a global leader in the medical communications space with a portfolio of clients across medical affairs, publications and commercial. We are part of Inizio Medical, which also includes ApotheCom, Nucleus Global and MEDiSTRAVA. Our position as part of this international network gives us a key advantage over other agencies in terms of the scale of our reach and depth of our expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More broadly, Inizio Medical is part of Inizio, whose mission is to be THE strategic partner for health and life sciences companies. Unparalleled in scale and expertise, we connect a full suite of Advisory, Medical, Marketing/Communications, Patient and Stakeholder Engagement, and Biotech services to reimagine clients&#39; challenges into opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;If you&#39;re an experienced healthcare communications professional with a passion for scientific publications and building trusted client relationships, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;As a Senior Account Manager, you&#39;ll lead the delivery of strategic publications programs for one or more pharmaceutical clients. Acting as the primary client contact, you&#39;ll oversee publication plans from concept to execution, ensuring projects are delivered on time, within budget, and to the highest quality standards. Working closely with scientific, editorial, and operational teams, you&#39;ll help clients achieve their communication objectives while driving account success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;At Ashfield MedComms, we offer flexible ways of working, whether that&#39;s remotely, in the office, or a hybrid of both, empowering our people to work in the way that suits them best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here&#39;s What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead day-to-day management of one or more publications accounts, acting as the primary client contact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oversee the delivery of publication plans, including manuscripts, abstracts, posters, and congress deliverables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build strong client relationships, providing proactive guidance and strategic support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage project timelines, budgets, and financial performance to ensure successful delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with scientific, editorial, and production teams to deliver high-quality publications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify opportunities to grow accounts and contribute to new business activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support and mentor junior team members while promoting best practices across the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5–7+ years&#39; experience in medical or healthcare communications, with a strong focus on scientific publications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong understanding of publication planning and the pharmaceutical industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven experience managing complex publications programmes and client relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Confident managing project budgets, timelines, and multiple priorities simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication, organisation, and stakeholder management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Medical Writer - Publications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashfield MedComms, an exciting and innovative leader in the field of medical communications, is growing! We are seeking a Senior Medical Writer to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our success has led to continued expansion both in the range of services we offer and our global presence. We are now looking for a talented and enthusiastic Senior Medical Writer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Medical Writer, you will use your scientific expertise to develop and deliver innovative medical communications projects. This is an excellent opportunity for an experienced medical writer seeking professional growth and progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Taking the lead role in projects where required and taking ownership for the scientific / editorial component, you will be responsible for producing high-quality scientific content for a range of printed and computer-based scientific materials from technical manuscripts to congress materials, interactive web projects and sales aids.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve reviewing and interpreting data from preclinical and clinical research articles and clinical study reports as the basis of creating scientific written materials in keeping with project briefs.&amp;nbsp; As a Senior Medical Writer, you will assist with editing and proofreading of text written by other team members and provide constructive feedback to aid learning and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with leading international pharmaceutical clients, you will be interacting with some of the world’s leading scientists and physicians on critical therapeutic and scientific issues. You will be required to participate in client meetings / teleconferences and attend scientific meetings such as congress, symposia and advisory boards and participate in pre-meetings, onsite activities and post meeting work as required, autonomously as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about communicating science then this is your opportunity to advance your career and have real input, making cutting-edge science accessible to those who need it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To succeed you will have an advanced degree in the life sciences (PhD, MD or PharmD is mandatory), as well as at least two years of relevant medical information, communications or marketing writing experience (agency or pharmaceutical).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to a competitive package, we are known for our friendly and informal working environment. We also offer excellent opportunities for career and personal development, and a robust benefits package including health, dental, vision, 401(K), vacation, holiday, and sick time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At Ashfield MedComms, &lt;/strong&gt;we value inclusivity, recognize the power of diversity and inspire the next generation of change-makers. We are an equal opportunities employer. We believe in creating a dynamic work environment that values diversity, equity and inclusion. We aim to recruit from a diverse slate of candidates and foster an environment that provides the right conditions for long-term success. We welcome all applications regardless of race, color, religion or belief, gender, gender identity, age, national origin, marital status, military veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation and physical or mental disability.&lt;/p&gt;
